member.summary:
To enable TLS 1.2 the ServicePointManager.SecurityProtocol property must be set: ServicePointManager.SecurityProtocol = SecurityProtocolType.Tls | SecurityProtocolType.Tls11 | SecurityProtocolType.Tls12;
However, this setting cannot be applied to individual requests but rather is set for the current AppDomain. In order to avoid conflicts this property is set within Httphandler which is run in a separate AppDomain.
The use of MarshallableCompletionSource is required due to it not being possible to make cross-domain calls for methods with a non-serializable return type such as Task. See the following for details:
